  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, propagation-based methods exhibit a more robust performance against malicious entities compared to style-based methods.",
    "However, they may be less effective in early detection of disinformation (Zhou and Zafarani 2020).",
    "Therefore, hybrid methods leverage a combination of content-based features and context-based features to address the limitations of each method and thereby deliver a more efficient detection model.",
    "The goal of the detection approach is to identify disinformation on social networks, which is typically conducted after the news has been written and disseminated.",
    "Hence, if the detection process is not carried out promptly, it can result in the widespread dissemination of disinformation, allowing its adverse effects to become more entrenched and lasting."
  ],
